          "severity": "medium",
          "rule_version": "FFOX-00-000007",
          "rule_title": "Firefox must be configured to disable form fill assistance.",
          "fix_text": "Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Disable Form History\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>DisableFormHistory</key>\n<true/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableFormHistory\": true",
          "reference_identifier": null,
          "group_title": "Firefox must be configured to disable form fill assistance.",
          "false_positives": "",
          "false_negatives": "",
          "discussion": "To protect privacy and sensitive data, Firefox provides the ability to configure the program so that data entered into forms is not saved. This mitigates the risk of a website gleaning private information from prefilled information.",
          "check_content": "Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window.\n\nIf \"DisableFormHistory\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.",
          "documentable": "",
          "mitigations": "",
          "potential_impacts": "",
          "third_party_tools": "Xylok",
          "mitigation_control": "",
          "responsibility": "",
          "security_override_guidance": "",
          "ia_controls": "",
          "check_content_ref": null,
          "legacy_ids": [
