          "weight": "10.0",
          "classification": "Unclassified",
          "severity": "medium",
          "rule_version": "FFOX-00-000025",
          "rule_title": "Firefox Enhanced Tracking Protection must be enabled.",
          "fix_text": "Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Preferences\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value:\n{\n  \"browser.contentblocking.category\": {\n    \"Value\": \"strict\",\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>Preferences</key>\n<dict>\n  <key>browser.contentblocking.category</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Value</key>\n    <string>strict</string>\n    <key>Status</key>\n    <string>locked</string>\n  </dict>\n</dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Preferences\": {\n  \"browser.contentblocking.category\": {\n    \"Value\": \"strict\",\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}",
          "reference_identifier": null,
          "group_title": "Firefox Enhanced Tracking Protection must be enabled.",
          "false_positives": "",
          "false_negatives": "",
          "discussion": "Tracking generally refers to content, cookies, or scripts that can collect browsing data across multiple sites.\n\nIt is detrimental for applications to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nApplications are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions).\n\nExamples of nonessential capabilities include but are not limited to advertising software or browser plug-ins that are not related to requirements or provide a wide array of functionality not required for every mission but that cannot be disabled.",
          "check_content": "Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar.\n\nIf \"Preferences\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not include \"browser.contentblocking.category\" with a value of  \"strict\" and status of \"locked\", this is a finding.",
          "documentable": "",
          "mitigations": "",
          "potential_impacts": "",
          "third_party_tools": "Xylok",
          "mitigation_control": "",
          "responsibility": "",
          "security_override_guidance": "",
          "ia_controls": "",
          "check_content_ref": null,
          "legacy_ids": [
            "V-251569"
          ],
          "ccis": [
            "CCI-000381"
          ],
          "group_tree": [
            {
              "id": "V-251569",
              "title": "SRG-APP-000141",
              "description": "<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"
            }
          ],
          "createdAt": "2026-03-28T04:09:31Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-03-28T04:09:31Z",
          "status": "open",
          "overrides": {},
          "comments": "Mozilla Firefox is not configured to enable Enhanced Tracking Protection.",
          "finding_details": "#if [ -e /etc/firefox/policies/policies.json ];\nthen\n    echo \"/etc/firefox/policies/policies.json exists.\"\n    echo \"***XYLOK ICS***\"\n    cat /etc/firefox/policies/policies.json\nelse\n    echo \"/etc/firefox/policies/policies.json does not exist.\"\n    echo \"***XYLOK ICS***\"\n    if [ -e \"$ffinstloc/distribution/policies.json\" ];\n    then\n        echo \"$ffinstloc/distribution/policies.json exists.\"\n        echo \"***XYLOK ICS***\"\n        cat \"$ffinstloc/distribution/policies.json\"\n    else\n        echo \"$ffinstloc/distribution/policies.json does not exist.\"\n    fi\nfi\n\n\ud83d\udd0d /etc/firefox/policies/policies.json does not exist.\n\u274c /usr/lib64/firefox/distribution/policies.json does not exist.\n\n\nXylok post-processing completed with no errors.\n\n\nXylok post-processing completed with no errors.\n"
        },
        {
          "uuid": "9373f4d2-2118-4076-b250-cc1efaa86976",
